ality, and ethnicity at the hub of Bangkok's modern economy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCapitalismxSocial aspectszThailandzBangkok. 0aGlobalization. 0aSex rolezThailandzBangkok. 0aWomenzThailandxEconomic conditions. 0aWomenzThailandxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aamway.  aanthropological study.  aanthropologists.  aavon ladies.  aavon.  abangkok.  abusiness relationships.  acapitalism.  acase studies.  acommerce and business.  acontemporary bangkok.  adepartment stores.  aeconomic boom.  aeconomic development.  aeconomic expansion.  aeconomic history.  aethnographers.  aethnography.  afeminist theory.  aglobal economy.  aglobalization.  agogo bars.  aidentities.  amalls.  amodern lifestyles.  amodern markets.  aprivate life.  apublic life.  asex workers.  atelecommunications.  atextbooks.  athai society.  athailand.  atomboys.  atycoons.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093743740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520937437423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520937437/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles